{"user_message": {"title": "ADR 0006 — Stabilization Handoff: Home-Link Guard (cert-3, ai-bookkeeper)", "content": "## ADR 0006 — Stabilization: home-route link & navigation guard

**Mode:** TEAM HANDOFF (Solution Architect = scoper; Dev Clone implements). Grounded in the committed tree, not the seed's description.

### Context
Seed reports a `@next/next/no-html-link-for-pages` regression — a raw `<a href="/">` in `src/app/page.tsx` that held the last two releases (cert-1 shipped it via scope-creep, cert-2 held formatMoney on it).

**Empirical finding — the defect is NOT present in the committed tree:**
- `src/app/page.tsx:12` already uses `<Link href="/">` (next/link imported at `:2`).
- All internal page routes already use `<Link>`: `/`, `/pricing` (l.35/119/366/429), `/faq` (l.38/435), `/dashboard` (l.41/409/441).
- The only raw `<a>` tags target **hash anchors** (`#how`, `#start` — l.31/45/106/401), which the rule does **not** flag.
- **`eslint .` exits 0 — trunk is already GREEN.**

The `<a>`→`<Link>` conversion the seed requests is a no-op. The real gap is the *absence of a behavioral guard*, which is why this debt churned across two certs.

### Decision
**Do not modify `page.tsx`** (already correct; touching it = unjustified churn). Lock in the fix with the minimal increment the seed explicitly asked for: **one focused Playwright e2e test** asserting the home/brand link performs client-side navigation back to `/`. `eslint .` remains the structural guard and is already in the quality gate.

*Considered & rejected:* React-render unit test (testing-library/jsdom not installed → would be scope creep); editing `page.tsx` (no raw page-link `<a>` to convert).

### Consequences
Trunk stays green; a regression guard now exists. New file only; `page.tsx` untouched. Non-functional → **PATCH**.

> ⚠️ **Version flag for Release Manager:** current `package.json` version is **0.4.0**. A PATCH is **0.4.1** — the seed's stated **0.5.x** would be a MINOR, not a PATCH. Recommend **0.4.1**. Versioning is the Release Manager's call.

---

## Task breakdown (1 task · 1 story point)

### Task 1 — Add home-navigation regression guard e2e test (1 pt) → Dev Clone
**Create:** `e2e/home-nav.spec.ts` (new file only).
**Do NOT modify:** `src/app/page.tsx`, any component, `eslint.config.mjs`, `package.json`, or any other file.

**What to write** — follow the existing `@playwright/test` convention (see `e2e/dashboard.spec.ts`); webServer + baseURL auto-boot via `playwright.config.ts` (port 3100):
```ts
import { test, expect } from "@playwright/test";

// Regression guard for ADR 0006: the home/brand link must be a real next/link
// client-route, not a raw <a> (which @next/next/no-html-link-for-pages forbids).
test.describe("home navigation", () => {
  test("brand link returns to / via client navigation", async ({ page }) => {
    await page.goto("/pricing");
    // tag the page; a full document reload would clear this flag
    await page.evaluate(() => ((window as any).__noReload = true));
    await page.getByRole("link", { name: /Ledgerline/ }).first().click();
    await expect(page).toHaveURL(/\/$/);
    expect(await page.evaluate(() => (window as any).__noReload)).toBe(true); // SPA nav, no reload
    await expect(page.getByRole("heading", { level: 1 })).toBeVisible();
  });
});
```
If the `__noReload` flag proves flaky against the dev server, fall back to asserting only `toHaveURL(/\/$/)` + the H1 visible — navigation correctness is the contract; the no-reload check is the bonus.

**Edge cases:** the brand link text "Ledgerline" also appears in the footer — `.first()` pins to the header link. The `/pricing` route must exist (it does).

**Validation commands (all must pass):**
```bash
npm run lint        # eslint . → must stay exit 0 (the no-html-link guard)
npm run typecheck   # tsc --noEmit
npm run e2e         # playwright — new home-nav spec green
```

**Definition of done:** new spec passes; `git diff --stat` shows ONLY `e2e/home-nav.spec.ts` added; `src/app/page.tsx` unchanged.

### Out of scope (do NOT bundle)
ADR 0005 money-formatting consolidation · converting `#how`/`#start` hash anchors · any visual/copy refresh · adding a testing-library harness.

**Summary:** ADR 0006 (Accepted) · key decision: regression already fixed in tree, lock it with 1 guard test, no `page.tsx` change · **1 task / 1 point** · PATCH **0.4.1** (not 0.5.x — flagged).", "content_type": "success", "priority": "normal"}}

